<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="172" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,310,644,670]" box="[189,310,644,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,644,670]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="172" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,644,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,691,753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">The new species can be distinguished from its congeners by the smaller size (9.5‒10.0 mm), and the distally narrowed forewing with costal margin concave beyond middle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1315,793,866]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,324,793,819]" box="[189,324,793,819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,793,819]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="172" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,793,819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1315,839,866]" box="[189,1315,839,866]" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[725,852,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="172">minisculus</emphasis>
, referring to the small size of the adult.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
